    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2020-06-11</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2020-06-15T15:39:49Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This resolution expresses support for freedom of the press and opposes the targeting of journalists.</p> <p>Specifically, the resolution</p> <ul> <li>calls on law enforcement to protect freedom of the press and refrain from targeting journalists and media workers;</li> <li> calls on government entities to clarify that credentialed press are exempt from curfews enacted in response to protests and public demonstrations; </li> <li> stresses the need for accountability where law enforcement entities or protesters violate the Constitution, laws, or regulations in their treatment of journalists and media crews during protests; and </li> <li> reaffirms the centrality of freedom of the press to supporting democracy, exposing corruption, and promoting good governance. </li> </ul>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2020-06-11T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
